---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">About POTM</h1>

  <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-gray-700">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">What is POTM?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        POTM (Player of the Match) is a simple voting app for sports teams.
        After a match, share a link with your team and let everyone vote for
        their player of the match — no sign-up required for voters.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">How it works</h2>
      <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>
          <strong>Create an account</strong> — Sign in with your Google account
          to manage your squads.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Create a squad</strong> — Set up your team with a name,
          description, and optional header image.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Add players</strong> — Add your team's players to the squad
          roster.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Create a fixture</strong> — Before or after a match, create a
          fixture with the opponent name, select which players were in the squad,
          and set a voting deadline.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Share the vote link</strong> — Copy the voting link and share
          it with your team via WhatsApp, email, or wherever your team
          communicates.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>View results</strong> — Admins can see live results at any
          time. Everyone else sees the winner after the voting deadline.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Multi-admin support</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Invite other managers to help run your squad. Admins can manage players,
        create fixtures, and view results. The squad owner can invite and remove
        admins.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Open source</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        POTM is open source. Check out the code on
        <a
          href="https://github.com/leggetter/potm"
          class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700 underline"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
